name: Owl

flavor_text: "You can't keep me away from the fun!"

text:
Support (Whenever this character quests, you may add their {S} to another chosen character's {S} this turn.)

WE'RE PIRATES, YOU SEE Whenever this character quests, you pay 1 {I} less for the next Pirate character you play this turn.

name: Gopher
flavor_text: "I keep fixin' this same ding-danged hole! I should start charging overtime, plus 10 percent."

name: Simba
flavor_text: "Look at that water, and those birds! Wow. Wait 'til Timon and Pumbaa see this!"

name: Chip
text: DALE'S PARTNER When you play this character, chosen character gets +1 {L} this turn.
flavor_text: "Come on, Dale—this is no time for hanging around!"

name: Dale
text: CHIP'S PARTNER This character enters play exerted unless you have a character named Chip in play.
flavor_text: "But Chip, hanging around is what I do best!"

name: David

flavor_text: "Grab a board and come on out! Choice waves today."

name: Prince Naveen
text:
Shift 3 (You may pay 3 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Prince Naveen.)
Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)

name: Prince Naveen
flavor_text: "Dance little friends—fill the air with light and joy. Achidanza! It is like seeing music come to life."

name: Chip
text: THE VALUE OF FRIENDSHIP While you have a character named Dale in play, this character gains Support. (Whenever they quest, you may add their {S} to another chosen character's {S} this turn.)

name: Monterey Jack
flavor_text: "There's only one thing I like more than cheese—nothin'."

text:
Shift 5 (You may pay 5 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Chip or Dale.)
(This character counts as being named both Chip and Dale.)
SEARCH AND RESCUE During your turn, whenever a card is put into your inkwell, you may return a character card from your discard to your hand.

name: Judy Hopps
text:
Support (Whenever this character quests, you may add their {S} to another chosen character's {S} this turn.)

NEED SOME HELP? At the end of your turn, you may ready another chosen character of yours.

name: Tiana
text: SPECIAL RESERVATION Whenever a character of yours is challenged while this character is exerted, the challenging character gets -3 {S} this turn unless their player pays 3 {I}.
flavor_text: "The only way to get what you want in this world is through hard work."

name: Grand Councilwoman
text: FIND IT! Whenever this character quests, your other Alien characters get +1 {L} this turn.
flavor_text: "I want an expert on this planet in here now!"

name: Dale

name: Nani
text:
Support (Whenever this character quests, you may add their {S} to another chosen character’s {S} this turn.)
I AM SO SORRY 2 {I} - Chosen character gets -1 {S} until the start of your next turn.

name: Simba
text:
Shift 3 (You may pay 3 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Simba.)
UNDERSTAND THE BALANCE At the end of your turn, if this character is exerted, you may ready your other characters.

text: SAFE AND SOUND Whenever this character quests, choose a character of yours and that character can't be challenged until the start of your next turn.
flavor_text: "My, you've had an awfully big adventure. Now it's time to rest."

name: Rabbit
text: BE MORE CAREFUL When you play this character, you may remove up to 1 damage from chosen character.
flavor_text: "See? I told you it was dangerous out there!"

name: Roo
text: I'M A PIRATE TOO! When you play this character, you may give chosen character -2 {S} until the start of your next turn.
flavor_text: "Look at all my ships, mama! We're going on the Azurite Sea!"

name: Mr. Litwak
text: THE GANG'S ALL HERE Once during your turn, whenever you play another character, you may ready this character. He can’t quest or challenge for the rest of this turn.
flavor_text: "Come on in. Good to see you."

name: Jim Hawkins
text:
Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)
HIRE A CREW When you play this character, look at the top 4 cards of your deck. You may reveal any number of Pirate character cards and put them into your hand. Put the rest on the bottom of your deck in any order.

name: Stitch
text: NEED A HAND? 1 {I} - This character gets +1 {S} this turn.
flavor_text: Always ready in an emergency—usually because he caused it.

name: Good Job!
text: Chosen character gets +1 {L} this turn.
flavor_text:
"Be proud of that badge. You earned it."
—Judy Hopps

name: I Won't Give In
text:
(A character with cost 2 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Return a character card with cost 2 or less from your discard to your hand.
flavor_text: 'Til I reach the end, and then I'll start again

name: Rescue Rangers Away!
text: Count the number of characters you have in play. Chosen character loses {S} equal to that number until the start of your next turn.

name: Safe and Sound
text: Chosen character of yours can’t be challenged until the start of your next turn.
flavor_text: "Here I am, mama!"

name: Naveen's Ukulele
text: MAKE IT SING 1 {I}, Banish this item - Chosen character counts as having +3 cost to sing songs this turn.
flavor_text:
"I love this instrument! I strum, everyone dances."
—Prince Naveen

name: Pooh Pirate Ship
text: MAKE A RESCUE {E}, 3 {I} – Return a Pirate character card from your discard to your hand.
flavor_text: The friendliest ship on the Azurite Sea.

name: Scrump
text: I MADE HER {E} one of your characters - Chosen character gets -2 {S} until the start of your next turn.
flavor_text:
"Her head is too big. So I pretend a bug laid eggs in her ears..."
—Lilo

name: Hundred Acre Island
text: FRIENDS FOREVER During an opponent's turn, whenever a character is banished here, gain 1 lore.

name: Sugar Rush Speedway
text: BRING IT HOME, LITTLE ONE! When you move a character here from another location, you may banish this location to gain 3 lore and draw 3 cards.

name: Hades

flavor_text: "You could say I'm big on the catch, not so much on the release."

name: Madam Mim
text:
Challenger +1 (While challenging, this character gets +1 {S}.)
ZIM ZABBERIM ZIM Your other characters gain Challenger +1.

name: Genie
flavor_text: "For the indecisive sailor we have three, count 'em, three ships in one! It sails, it flies, it juliennes fries! All for the low price of just one wish."

name: Sisu
text: Challenger +2 (While challenging, this character gets +2 {S}).
flavor_text: "I'm a water dragon. This is water. It's sort of my thing."

name: The White Rose
text: THE BEAUTY OF THE WORLD When you play this character, gain 1 lore.
flavor_text:
"You can learn a lot of things from the flowers..."
—Alice

name: Juju
text: BEES' KNEES When you play this character, move 1 damage counter from chosen character to chosen opposing character.
flavor_text:
"Juju! You get yourself out of that there magic, you bad boy!"
—Mama Odie

name: Rafiki
flavor_text: "The signs, they never lie. The snake thinks he's planned for everything... Oh, ho, ho! He forgot about the owl. There's hope yet!"

name: Tinker Bell
text: Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)
flavor_text: She zips through the waves without a drop of water touching her.

name: The Carpenter
text: I'LL GET YOU! When this character is banished, you may exert chosen character.
flavor_text: The Carpenter's stomach growled as he clenched his hammer tight...

name: Iago
text: GUESS WHO When this character is banished in a challenge, return this card to your hand.
flavor_text: "You think you can get rid of me that easy?!"

name: The Walrus
flavor_text: ... While the Walrus finished off the lot, down to the final bite.

name: Scar
text:
Rush (This character can challenge the turn they're played.)
Challenger +3 (While challenging, this character gets +3 {S}.)

name: Tinker Bell
text:
Shift 5 (You may pay 5 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Tinker Bell.)
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)
SHINING EXAMPLE Whenever this character quests, your other Fairy characters get +1 {L} this turn.

text: FLY, MY PET! When this character is banished, you may draw a card.
flavor_text:
"Go, and do not fail me."
—Maleficent

name: March Hare
text: Rush (This character can challenge the turn they're played.)
flavor_text: "Clear the table? Don't mind if I do!"

name: Magic Carpet
flavor_text:
"Carpet's always come through for us before! He won't let us down now." 
—Jasmine

name: Rafiki
text:
Shift 7 (You may pay 7 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Rafiki.)

text:
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)

name: Madam Mim
text: OH, BAT GIZZARDS 2 {I}, Choose and discard a card - Gain 1 lore.

flavor_text: "One of these has got to work. Let's see what happens."

name: Mama Odie
text: I HAVE TO DO EVERYTHING AROUND HERE Whenever you play a song, you may move up to 2 damage counters from chosen character to chosen opposing character.

name: Peter Pan
text: GOTCHA! During your turn, whenever a card is put into your inkwell, exert chosen opposing character.
flavor_text: "You're not getting away from me this time!"

name: Mad Hatter
text: WE'LL HAVE TO LOOK INTO THIS Whenever this character quests, you may look at the top card of chosen player's deck. Put it on top of their deck or into their discard.

name: A Very Merry Unbirthday
text:
(A character with cost 1 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Each opponent puts the top 2 cards of their deck into their discard.
flavor_text:
Now blow the candle out, my dear
And make your wish come true

name: Genie
text:
Shift 5 (You may pay 5 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Genie.)
YOUR REWARD AWAITS Whenever you play a card, draw a card.
FORBIDDEN TREASURE At the end of your turn, put all the cards in your hand on the bottom of your deck in any order.

—Mama Odie

—Alice

text:
For each Sorcerer character you have in play, you pay 1 {I} less to play this action.
Draw 2 cards.
flavor_text:
"I see the other half, in the Inklands. Quick, my tiny companion! Fetch me that crown!"
—Jafar

flavor_text:

Mad Hatter: "No, no, my dear—the cup missed the tea!"

Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)

Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.)

name: Goofy
text:
Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.)
CLEVER DESIGN Whenever this character quests, chosen character gains Ward until the start of your next turn.

Shift 4 (You may pay 4 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Basil.)

text: Each opponent discards all cards in their hand.
flavor_text: "At last! This is where your luck runs out!"

text: Chosen character gets +2 {S} this turn. If a Pirate character is chosen, they get +3 {S} instead.

"Bring me the treasure, bring me that ship, and bring me Peter Pan!"
—Captain Hook

text:
(A character with cost 2 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Chosen opposing character can't quest during their next turn. Draw a card.
flavor_text: If honey's what you covet, you'll find that they love it

text: Put 1 damage counter on chosen character.
flavor_text: "Don't move. A mosquito has chosen me as her perch. She's so... beautiful."

text: Ready chosen character.
flavor_text:
"Nobody gets left behind."
—Stitch

HAPPY FACE This item enters play exerted.
DESTROY! {E}, Banish this item - Choose one:
* Banish chosen item.
* Banish chosen damaged character.

"We've reinvented the very concept of transportation."
—Alistair Krei

text:
TEAMWORK For each character you have here, you pay 1 {I} less for the first action you play each turn.
LOTS TO LEARN Whenever you play a second action in a turn, gain 3 lore.

name: Mickey Mouse
text:
Shift 3 (You may pay 3 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Mickey Mouse.)
MARINER’S MIGHT Whenever this character quests, chosen Pirate character gets +2 {S} and gains "This character takes no damage from challenges" this turn.

text: Rush (This character can challenge the turn they're played.)

Moana: "Do you think they saw us?"
Maui: "They saw us."

name: Jasmine
text: YOU'LL NEVER MISS IT Whenever this character quests, each opponent loses 1 lore.
flavor_text: Even the smallest mouse can make the biggest difference.

name: Raya

name: Wendy Darling
text:
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)
LOOK LIVELY, CREW! While you have another Pirate character in play, this character gets +1 {S} and +1 {L}.

name: Michael Darling
flavor_text: "Hoist the colors! Prepare to fight! Teddy bear at the ready!"

name: Aladdin
flavor_text: Finding your way through the Azurite Sea takes a stout heart, plenty of courage, and more than a little luck.

name: Markowski
text: Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)
flavor_text: "Just what we needed—a new place to fight bugs."

name: Abu
text: Rush (This character can challenge the turn they’re played.)
flavor_text:
"Port, Abu! Port! To the left! ABU! The other way!"
—Aladdin

name: Mickey Mouse
text: SOLID GROUND While this character is at a location, he gets +2 {S}.
flavor_text: "Golly, this looked a lot easier from the ship. But I know I can make it—the crew is counting on me!"

name: Adorabeezle Winterpop
text: KEEP DRIVING While this character has damage, she gets +1 {L}.
flavor_text: "It'll take more than that to knock me out of the race!"

name: Moana
text: LEARNING THE ROPES This character can't challenge unless you have a Captain character in play.
flavor_text: "You wanna tell me I don't know what I'm doing? I know I don't!"

name: John Darling
flavor_text: "Get ready, Michael! Here they come!"

name: Aladdin
text:
Shift 2 (You may pay 2 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Aladdin.)

text: LAND, HO! Once during your turn, whenever a card is put into your inkwell, you may return a location card from your discard to your hand.
flavor_text: Minnie leaned forward. Could it be true? Was this the island at last?

name: Moana
text:
Shift 5 (You may pay 5 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Moana.)
GATHERING FORCES When you play this character, you may move any number of your characters to the same location for free. Gain 1 lore for each character you moved.

name: Goofy
text:
Rush (This character can challenge the turn they're played.)

name: Tigger
text:
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)

name: Lead the Way
text: Your characters get +2 {S} this turn.

name: The Islands I Pulled from the Sea

(A character with cost 3 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Search your deck for a location card, reveal that card to all players, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Energy Blast
text: Banish chosen character. Draw a card.
flavor_text:
"Did you really think I would fight fair?"
—Jafar

name: Longboat
text: TAKE IT FOR A SPIN 2 {I} – Chosen character of yours gains Evasive until the start of your next turn. (Only characters with Evasive can challenge them.)

name: Gold Coin
text: GLITTERING ACCESS {E}, 1 {I}, Banish this item – Ready chosen character of yours. They can't quest for the rest of this turn.
flavor_text:
"Sweet mother of monkey milk! A gold coin!"
—Vanellope von Schweetz

name: Card Soldier's Spear

name: Skull Rock
text:

name: B.E.N.

Shift 4 (You may pay 4 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Gadget Hackwrench.)

flavor_text: "As the duly appointed representative for the Galactic Council, I volunteer for this assignment!"

name: Hiro Hamada
text: SWEET TECH {2} {E} - Search your deck for an item card or a Robot character card and reveal it to all players. Shuffle your deck and put that card on top of it.
flavor_text: "A couple more tweaks and I've just about . . . got it!"

name: Heihei
text:
EAT ANYTHING When you play this character, exert chosen opposing item. It can't ready at the start of its next turn.
OUT TO LUNCH During your turn, this character gains Evasive. (They can challenge characters with Evasive.)

name: Sour Bill
text: UNPALATABLE When you play this character, chosen opposing character gets -2 {S} this turn.
flavor_text: "You want to go in there? Fine. If you do, you won't come back out."

name: Nick Wilde
text: NICE TO HAVE A PARTNER While you have another character with Support in play, this character gets +2 {S}.
flavor_text: "Glad you could make it."

name: Wasabi
text:
BLADES OF FURY When you play this character, you may banish chosen item. Its player gains 1 lore.
QUICK REFLEXES During your turn, this character gains Evasive. (They can challenge characters with Evasive.)

name: Nick Wilde
text:
Shift 1 (You may pay 1 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Nick Wilde.)
CAN'T TOUCH ME While you have an item in play, this character can't be challenged.

name: Gadget Hackwrench
flavor_text: "All the clues pointed to an island, but I never thought I'd see it on a map. Golly, this is incredible! I mean, the island actually exists, so it's technically credible—but still! This is amazing!"

name: Dr. Delbert Doppler
flavor_text: "Of course! All of this is perfectly logical. That's why my old star atlases are useless. Here, every star in the sky is different!"

name: Tadashi Hamada
text: LET'S GET BACK TO WORK This character gets +1 {S} and +1 {W} for each item you have in play.
flavor_text: "I'm not giving up on you. You don't understand this yet, but people need you."

name: Hiro Hamada
text:
I NEED TO UPGRADE ALL OF YOU Your other Inventor characters gain Resist +1. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1.)

SHAPE THE FUTURE 2 {I} - Look at the top card of your deck. Put it on either the top or the bottom of your deck.

name: Tadashi Hamada
text: SOMEONE HAS TO HELP During an opponent’s turn, when this character is banished, you may put the top card of your deck into your inkwell facedown. Then, put this card into your inkwell facedown.
flavor_text: His work lives on.

name: Baymax
text:
FULLY CHARGED If you have an Inventor character in play, you pay 1 {I} less to play this character.
YOU SAID 'OW' 2 {I} - Remove up to 1 damage from another chosen character.

name: Baymax
text: THE TREATMENT IS WORKING When you play this character and whenever he quests, you may remove up to 2 damage from another chosen character of yours. Gain 1 lore for each 1 damage removed this way.

name: Yokai
flavor_text: "You are all brilliant scientists and inventors. Think of what you could do with this little device. How do you push the boundaries of what is possible?"

name: Hiram Flaversham
flavor_text: He will find a way to make everything mouse-sized.

name: Yokai
text:
Shift 6 (You may pay 6 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Yokai.)
NEUROTRANSMITTER You may play items named Microbots for free.
TECHNICAL GAIN Whenever this character quests, draw a card for each opposing character with {S}.

name: Alice
text:
Ward (Opponents can't choose this character except to challenge.)
AHOY! Whenever this character quests, another chosen character of yours gets +1 {L} and gains Ward until the start of your next turn.

name: We Could Be Immortals
text:
(A character with cost 4 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Your Inventor characters gain Resist +6 this turn. Then, put this card into your inkwell facedown and exerted. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 6.)

name: Sail The Azurite Sea
text: This turn, you may put an additional card from your hand into your inkwell facedown. Draw a card.
flavor_text: You need a good plan and even better luck to make it across these treacherous waters.

name: Helping Hand
text: Chosen character gains Support this turn. Draw a card. (Whenever they quest, you may add their {S} to another chosen character's {S} this turn.)
flavor_text:
"When you're making the world a better place, every little thing helps."
-Judy Hopps

name: Prepare Your Bot
text:
Choose one:
* Ready chosen item.
* Ready chosen Robot character. They can't quest for the rest of this turn.

name: Baymax's Healthcare Chip
text:
10,000 MEDICAL PROCEDURES {E} - Choose one:
* Remove up to 1 damage from chosen character. 
* If you have a Robot character in play, remove up to 3 damage from chosen character.

name: Microbots
text:
LIMITLESS APPLICATIONS You may have any number of cards named Microbots in your deck.
INSPIRED TECH When you play this item, chosen character gets -1 {S} this turn for each item named Microbots you have in play.

name: Jumbo Pop
text: HERE YOU GO Banish this item – Remove up to 2 damage from each of your characters. Draw a card.

name: Rescue Rangers Submarine
text: PLANNING SESSION At the start of your turn, if you have a character here, you may put the top card of your deck into your inkwell facedown and exerted.

name: Institute of Technology
text:
WELCOME TO THE LAB Inventor characters get +1 {W} while here.
PUSH THE BOUNDARIES At the start of your turn, if you have a character here, gain 1 lore.

name: Kakamora
text: A LITTLE HELP When you play this character, if you have another Pirate character in play, you may deal 1 damage to chosen character or location.
flavor_text:
"They're very good at making trouble."
-Maui

name: Kakamora
text: COCONUT LEADER Whenever this character quests, you may draw a card. Then, choose and discard a card to deal 1 damage to chosen character or location. If a Pirate character card was discarded, deal 3 damage to that character or location instead.

name: Jim Hawkins
text: COME HERE, COME HERE, COME HERE! During your turn, whenever a card is put into your inkwell, this character gets Challenger +2 this turn. (While challenging, this character gets +2 {S}.)

name: Mr. Big
text: REPUTATION This character can't be challenged by characters with 2 {S} or more.
flavor_text: "You have done me a great service."

name: Mr. Smee
text: GOOD CATCH During your turn, this character gains Evasive. (They can challenge characters with Evasive.)
flavor_text: "Captain Hook'd like a word with ya."

name: Mr. Smee
text:
Shift 4 (You may pay 4 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Mr. Smee.)
RAISE THE COLORS When you play this character, you may deal damage to chosen character equal to the number of your other Pirate characters in play.

name: Mullins
text: FALL IN LINE While you have a character named Mr. Smee in play, this character gains Resist +1. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1.)
flavor_text: "Anything for you, Mr. Smee! Except me share o' the plunder..."

name: Kohut
flavor_text: "Ma'am! I am a highly trained instrument of tactical superiority! Maybe we could find someone else for the gruntwork! Ma'am!"

name: King Hubert
flavor_text: "I told you we'd find an island eventually! Excellent navigating. Yes, yes, I'm quite proud. Now, a toast to our success!"

name: Hercules
text: Challenger +2 (While challenging, this character gets +2 {S}).
flavor_text: "That maze wasn't so bad! Let's see what this island has in store for us."

name: John Silver
text: HUNK OF HARDWARE When you play this character, chosen character can't challenge during their next turn.
flavor_text: "At the end of the day, it's the simplest tools that come through for you in a pinch."

name: Mr. Arrow
text: Resist +1 (Damage dealt to this character is reduced by 1.)
flavor_text: "We're holding steady, Captain. Despite this wind. And these waves."

name: Jim Hawkins
text:
Shift 3 (You may pay 3 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Jim Hawkins.)
BATTLE STATION When you play this character, you may deal 1 damage to chosen character or location.

name: Tuk Tuk
flavor_text:
Raya: "Nothing gets past Tuk Tuk. Nothing."
Sisu: "Except butterflies! Oh, and birds!"
Raya: "Fine. Most things don't get past Tuk Tuk."

name: Billy Bones
text: KEEP IT HIDDEN When this character is banished, you may banish chosen item or location.
flavor_text: "He'll be comin' soon. Can't let them find this."

name: Pluto
text:
Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)
BRAVO While this character has no damage, he gets +4 {S}.

name: Mickey Mouse
text: SUPPORT Your Pluto characters get Resist +1. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1.)
flavor_text: "Oh dear, Donald was right - it's creepy out here in the dark!"

name: Cobra Bubbles
text:
Bodyguard (This character may enter play exerted. An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)
THINK ABOUT WHAT'S BEST 2 {I} – Draw a card, then choose and discard a card.

name: Gantu
flavor_text: "The strength of the number is overrated. I have more confidence in my own strength."

name: Wreck-it Ralph
text: I WRECK THINGS Whenever this character quests, you may banish chosen item or location to gain 2 lore.
flavor_text: "I'm very good at what I do. Probably the best I know."

name: Calhoun
text:
Resist +1 (Damage dealt to this character is reduced by 1.)
LEVEL UP During your turn, whenever this character banishes another character in a challenge, gain 2 lore.

name: Captain Amelia
text:
DRIVELING GALOOTS This character can't be challenged by Pirate characters.
EVERYTHING SHIPSHAPE While being challenged, your other characters gain Resist +1. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1.)

name: Jafar
text: YOU WILL BE PAID WHEN THE TIME COMES During your turn, whenever a card is put into your inkwell, deal 1 damage to chosen character.
flavor_text: "The power of the shattered crown is formidable, but not enough. If I had both halves of the Hexwell Crown, I could rule all of Lorcana!"

name: John Silver
text:
Shift 5 (You may pay 5 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named John Silver.)
Resist +2 (Damage dealt to this character is reduced by 2.)
DON'T JUST SIT THERE! At the start of your turn, deal 1 damage to each opposing ready character.

name: Hot Potato
text:
Choose one:
- Deal 2 damage to chosen character.
- Banish chosen item.
flavor_text:
"This is not going to end well."
-Pleakley

name: I'm Still Here
text:
(A character with cost 3 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Chosen character gains Resist +2 until the start of your next turn. Draw a card. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 2.)

name: Twin Fire
text: Deal 2 damage to chosen character. Then, you may choose and discard a card to deal 2 damage to another chosen character.
flavor_text: "I got 'em!" "No, I got 'em!"

name: Ambush!
text: {E} one of your characters to deal damage equal to their {S} to chosen character.
flavor_text: Pirates will use any advantage they can get.

name: Unfortunate Situation
text: Each opponent chooses one of their characters and deals 4 damage to them.

name: King's Sensor Core
text:
SYMBOL OF ROYALTY Your Prince and King characters gain Resist +1. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1.)
ROYAL SEARCH {E}, 2 {I} – Reveal the top card of your deck. If it's a Prince or King character card, you may put that card into your hand. Otherwise, put it on the top of your deck.

name: Training Dummy
text: HANDLE WITH CARE {E}, 2 {I} – Chosen character gains Bodyguard until the start of your next turn. (An opposing character who challenges one of your characters must choose one with Bodyguard if able.)

name: Sunglasses
text: SPYCRAFT {E} - Draw a card, then choose and discard a card.
flavor_text: The coolest accessory for top agents.

name: Treasure Mountain
text: SECRET WEAPON At the start of your turn, deal damage to chosen character or location equal to the number of characters here.

name: Galactic Council Chamber
text: FEDERATION DECREE While you have an Alien or Robot character here, this location can’t be challenged.

name: Chip 'n' Dale
text:
Shift 5 (You may pay 5 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Chip or Dale.)
(This character counts as being named both Chip and Dale.)
SEARCH AND RESCUE During your turn, whenever a card is put into your inkwell, you may return a character card from your discard to your hand.

name: Tiana
text: SPECIAL RESERVATION Whenever a character of yours is challenged while this character is exerted, the challenging character gets -3 {S} this turn unless their player pays 3 {I}.

name: Sugar Rush Speedway
text: BRING IT HOME, LITTLE ONE! When you move a character here from another location, you may banish this location to gain 3 lore and draw 3 cards.

name: Rafiki
text:
Shift 7 (You may pay 7 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Rafiki.)
ASTRAL ATTUNEMENT During your turn, whenever a card is put into your inkwell, you may draw a card.

name: Yzma
text: FEEL THE POWER {E} - If you have fewer than 3 cards in your hand, draw until you have 3 cards in your hand.

name: Maleficent's Staff
text: BACK, FOOLS! Whenever one of your opponents’ characters, items, or locations is returned to their hand from play, gain 1 lore.

name: Daisy Duck
text: DISTANT SHORES Whenever one of your Pirate characters quests while at a location, draw a card.

name: Basil
text:
Shift 4 (You may pay 4 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Basil.)
TWISTS AND TURNS During your turn, whenever a card is put into your inkwell, you may pay 1 {I} to have chosen opponent choose and discard a card.

name: You Came Back
text: Ready chosen character.

name: Raya
text: COME ON, LET'S DO THIS Once during your turn, whenever a card is put into your inkwell, you may ready another chosen character of yours. They can't quest for the rest of this turn.

name: Tigger
text:
Evasive (Only characters with Evasive can challenge this character.)
SWASH YOUR BUCKLES Whenever you play an action, this character gets +1 {S} and +1 {L} this turn.

name: The Islands I Pulled From the Sea
text:
(A character with cost 3 or more can {E} to sing this song for free.)
Search your deck for a location card, reveal that card to all players, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Gadget Hackwrench
text:
Shift 4 (You may pay 4 {I} to play this on top of one of your characters named Gadget Hackwrench.)
MECHANICALLY SAVVY While you have 3 or more items in play, you pay 1 {I} less to play Inventor characters.

text:
FULLY CHARGED If you have an Inventor character in play, you pay 1 {I} less to play this character.

text:

text: I WRECK THINGS Whenever this character quests, you may banish chosen item or location to gain 2 lore.

name: Captain Amelia
text:
DRIVELING GALOOTS This character can’t be challenged by Pirate characters.
EVERYTHING SHIPSHAPE While being challenged, your other characters gain Resist +1. (Damage dealt to them is reduced by 1.)
